		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Neoism</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Neoism</b> is a parodistic <a href="/wiki/-ism" title="-ism">-ism</a>. It refers both to a specific subcultural network of artistic performance and media experimentalists, and more generally to a practical underground philosophy. It operates with collectively shared <a href="/wiki/Pseudonym" title="Pseudonym">pseudonyms</a> and <a href="/wiki/Cultural_identity" title="Cultural identity">identities</a>, <a href="/wiki/Prank" title="Prank" class="mw-redirect">pranks</a>, <a href="/wiki/Paradox" title="Paradox">paradoxes</a>, <a href="/wiki/Plagiarism" title="Plagiarism">plagiarism</a> and <a href="/wiki/Fake" title="Fake">fakes</a>, and has created multiple contradicting definitions of itself in order to defy categorization and historization.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
